# Documentation — read and maintain

User-facing docs live in [README.md](../../README.md) and [docs/](../../docs/). Keep them accurate when behaviour or public API changes.

## Before changing public API or user-visible behaviour

1. Skim [docs/README.md](../../docs/README.md) — pick the doc(s) affected by your change.
2. Prefer updating the **lowest complexity** doc that covers the feature; link from higher-level docs instead of duplicating.

## After changes — update these when relevant

| Change | Update |
|--------|--------|
| New/changed `StompClient` or `StompServer` API | [README.md](../../README.md) quick start, [client-guide.md](../../docs/client-guide.md) or [server-guide.md](../../docs/server-guide.md) |
| New Maven module or artifact rename | [README.md](../../README.md), [overview.md](../../docs/overview.md), [getting-started.md](../../docs/getting-started.md) |
| Purpose, philosophy, or handler boundaries | [overview.md](../../docs/overview.md) |
| Transport schemes, TLS, versions, SPI | [advanced-topics.md](../../docs/advanced-topics.md), [client-guide.md](../../docs/client-guide.md) |
| New doc file or learning path | [docs/README.md](../../docs/README.md), [README.md](../../README.md) doc table |
| STOMP terms or invariants | [domain-specification.md](../../docs/domain-specification.md) |
| Internal architecture only | [ARCHITECTURE.md](../../ARCHITECTURE.md) — not user guides |

## Complexity order (do not invert)

1. **README** — elevator pitch, quick start, links
2. **overview / getting-started** — purpose, modules, first working code
3. **client-guide / server-guide** — intermediate usage patterns
4. **advanced-topics** — SPI, JPMS, wire format, TLS

Put new detail in the deepest applicable layer; add a one-line pointer in shallower docs.

## Quality bar

- Examples must compile against the **current** public API (copy from tests when possible).
- Document **released** Maven coordinates; note SNAPSHOT only for building from source.
- No stale API names (e.g. old handler signatures) — grep docs when renaming types.
- Cross-link between docs; avoid copying large blocks in multiple files.

## What not to duplicate

- **ARCHITECTURE.md** — contributors and agents; module internals, CI, JPMS map
- **domain-specification.md** — ubiquitous language, not tutorials
- **README** — should not grow into a full manual; link to `docs/`

